The aggregate of all credits in a financial year does not exceed rupees one lakh; 
b. The aggregate of all withdrawals and transfers in a month does not exceed rupees ten thousand; 
c. The balance at any point of time does not exceed rupees fifty thousand; 
d. Remittances from abroad cannot be credited to Small Accounts without completing normal KYC formalities; 
e. Small accounts are valid for a period of 12 months initially which may be extended by another 12 months if the person provides proof of having applied for an Officially Valid 
Document (OVD). f.
